#. <html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta content="Pali text from the Mahāsaṅgīti Tipiṭaka Buddhavasse 2500" name="description"><title></title></head><body><div id="text" lang="pli"><section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-np14"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Nissaggiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on relinquishment"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Kosiyavagga"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs0.5"
msgid ""
msgstr "Monks’ Relinquishment"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs0.6"
msgid "14. Chabbassasikkhāpada"
msgstr "14. The training rule on six years"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs0.7"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.14.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.79"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2135"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū anuvassaṃ santhataṃ kārāpenti."
msgstr "At that time monks were getting blankets made every year."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "Te yācanabahulā viññattibahulā viharanti—"
msgstr "They kept on begging and asking,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.4"
msgid "“eḷakalomāni detha."
msgstr "“Give wool;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.5"
msgid "Eḷakalomehi attho”ti."
msgstr "we need wool.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People grumbled and complained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.7"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā anuvassaṃ santhataṃ kārāpessanti, "
"yācanabahulā viññattibahulā viharissanti—"
msgstr ""
"“How can the Sakyan ascetics get blankets made every year, begging and "
"asking,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "‘eḷakalomāni detha, eḷakalomehi attho’ti."
msgstr "‘Give wool; we need wool’?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.9"
msgid ""
"Amhākaṃ pana sakiṃ katāni santhatāni pañcapi chapi vassāni honti, yesaṃ no "
"dārakā uhadantipi ummihantipi undūrehipi khajjanti."
msgstr ""
"We only make blankets for ourselves every five or six years, even though our "
"children defecate and urinate on them and they are eaten by rats.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.10"
msgid ""
"Ime pana samaṇā sakyaputtiyā anuvassaṃ santhataṃ kārāpenti, yācanabahulā "
"viññattibahulā viharanti—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "‘eḷakalomāni detha, eḷakalomehi attho’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2136"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.12"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.15"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū anuvassaṃ santhataṃ kārāpessanti, yācanabahulā "
"viññattibahulā viharissanti—"
msgstr "“How can those monks act like this?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "‘eḷakalomāni detha, eḷakalomehi attho’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.228"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2137"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.17"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū te anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ "
"ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.18"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū anuvassaṃ santhataṃ kārāpenti, yācanabahulā "
"viññattibahulā viharanti—"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that some monks are acting like this?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.19"
msgid "‘eḷakalomāni detha, eḷakalomehi attho’”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.20"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.21"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha criticized them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.22"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā anuvassaṃ santhataṃ kārāpessanti, "
"yācanabahulā viññattibahulā viharissanti—"
msgstr ""
"How can those foolish men get blankets made every year, begging and asking,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.23"
msgid "‘eḷakalomāni detha, eḷakalomehi attho’ti."
msgstr "‘Give wool; we need wool’?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.24"
msgid "Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.25"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.25a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2138"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.80"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.26"
msgid "“Navaṃ pana bhikkhunā santhataṃ kārāpetvā chabbassāni dhāretabbaṃ."
msgstr "‘If a monk gets a new blanket made, he should keep it for six years."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.27"
msgid ""
"Orena ce channaṃ vassānaṃ taṃ santhataṃ vissajjetvā vā avissajjetvā vā aññaṃ "
"navaṃ santhataṃ kārāpeyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Whether that blanket has been given away or not, if he gets another new "
"blanket made in less than six years, he commits an offense entailing "
"relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2139"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs1.28"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.14.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2140"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu kosambiyaṃ gilāno hoti."
msgstr "At one time a certain monk in Kosambī was ill."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.2"
msgid "Ñātakā tassa bhikkhuno santike dūtaṃ pāhesuṃ—"
msgstr "His relatives sent him a message:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.3"
msgid "“āgacchatu bhadanto mayaṃ upaṭṭhahissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Come, Venerable, we’ll attend on you.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.4"
msgid "Bhikkhūpi evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "Other monks"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.5"
msgid "“gacchāvuso, ñātakā taṃ upaṭṭhahissantī”ti."
msgstr "urged him to go,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.6"
msgid "So evamāha—"
msgstr "but he said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.7"
msgid "“bhagavatā, āvuso, sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ—"
msgstr "“The Master has laid down a training rule"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.8"
msgid "‘navaṃ pana bhikkhunā santhataṃ kārāpetvā chabbassāni dhāretabban’ti."
msgstr "that a monk who gets a new blanket made must keep it for six years."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.9"
msgid "Ahañcamhi gilāno, na sakkomi santhataṃ ādāya pakkamituṃ."
msgstr "Because I’m sick, I’m not able to take my blanket when I travel."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.10"
msgid "Mayhañca vinā santhatā na phāsu hoti."
msgstr "And because I’m not comfortable without it,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.11"
msgid "Nāhaṃ gamissāmī”ti."
msgstr "I cannot go.”"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="2141"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.12"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They told the Master."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.13"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā "
"bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards he gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.14"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānassa bhikkhuno santhatasammutiṃ dātuṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to give a blanket-permission to a sick monk."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.15"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbā."
msgstr "And it should be given in this way."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.16"
msgid ""
"Tena gilānena bhikkhunā saṃghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā "
"vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā "
"evamassa vacanīyo—"
msgstr ""
"After approaching the Order, the sick monk should put his upper robe over "
"one shoulder and pay respect at the feet of the senior monks. He should then "
"squat on his heels, put the palms of his hands together, and say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.17"
msgid "‘ahaṃ, bhante, gilāno"
msgstr "‘Venerables, I’m sick."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.18"
msgid "na sakkomi santhataṃ ādāya pakkamituṃ."
msgstr "I’m not able to take my blanket when I travel."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.19"
msgid "Sohaṃ, bhante, saṃghaṃ santhatasammutiṃ yācāmī’ti."
msgstr "I ask the Order for a blanket-permission.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.20"
msgid "Dutiyampi yācitabbā."
msgstr "And he should ask a second"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.21"
msgid "Tatiyampi yācitabbā."
msgstr "and a third time."

#. <a class="wt-pa" id="2142"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.22"
msgid "Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṃgho ñāpetabbo—"
msgstr "A competent and capable monk should then inform the Order:"

#. </p><div class="kamma"><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.23"
msgid "‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "‘Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.81"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.24"
msgid "Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu gilāno na sakkoti santhataṃ ādāya pakkamituṃ."
msgstr ""
"This monk so-and-so is sick. He is not able to take his blanket when he "
"travels."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.25"
msgid "So saṃghaṃ santhatasammutiṃ yācati."
msgstr "He is asking the Order for a blanket-permission."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.26"
msgid ""
"Yadi saṃghassa pattakallaṃ, saṃgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno santhatasammutiṃ "
"dadeyya."
msgstr ""
"If it seems appropriate to the Order, the Order should give a blanket-"
"permission to monk so-and-so."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.27"
msgid "Esā ñatti."
msgstr "This is the motion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.229"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2143"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.28"
msgid "Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.29"
msgid "Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu gilāno na sakkoti santhataṃ ādāya pakkamituṃ."
msgstr ""
"This monk so-and-so is sick. He is not able to take his blanket when he "
"travels."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.30"
msgid "So saṃghaṃ santhatasammutiṃ yācati."
msgstr "He is asking the Order for a blanket-permission."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.31"
msgid "Saṃgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno santhatasammutiṃ deti."
msgstr "The Order gives a blanket-permission to monk so-and-so."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.32"
msgid ""
"Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno santhatasammutiyā dānaṃ, so "
"tuṇhassa;"
msgstr ""
"Any monk who approves of giving a blanket-permission to monk so-and-so "
"should remain silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.33"
msgid "yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya."
msgstr "Any monk who does not approve should say so."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2144"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.34"
msgid "Dinnā saṃghena itthannāmassa bhikkhuno santhatasammuti."
msgstr "The Order has given a blanket-permission to monk so-and-so."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.35"
msgid "Khamati saṃghassa, tasmā tuṇhī,"
msgstr "The Order approves and is therefore silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.36"
msgid "Kevametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti."
msgstr "I will remember it thus.’"

#. </p></div><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2145"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.37"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.37a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2146"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.38"
msgid "“Navaṃ pana bhikkhunā santhataṃ kārāpetvā chabbassāni dhāretabbaṃ."
msgstr "‘If a monk gets a new blanket made, he should keep it for six years."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.39"
msgid ""
"Orena ce channaṃ vassānaṃ taṃ santhataṃ vissajjetvā vā avissajjetvā vā aññaṃ "
"navaṃ santhataṃ kārāpeyya, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, nissaggiyaṃ "
"pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Whether that blanket has been given away or not, if he gets another new "
"blanket made in less than six years, except if the monks have agreed, he "
"commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs2.40"
msgid "(<em>14</em>:<strong>33</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.14.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2147"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.1"
msgid "Navaṃ nāma"
msgstr "New:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.2"
msgid "karaṇaṃ upādāya vuccati."
msgstr "newly made is what is meant."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2148"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.3"
msgid "Santhataṃ nāma"
msgstr "A blanket:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.4"
msgid "santharitvā kataṃ hoti avāyimaṃ."
msgstr "it is made by spreading out, not by weaving."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2149"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.5"
msgid "Kārāpetvāti"
msgstr "Gets made:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.6"
msgid "karitvā vā kārāpetvā vā."
msgstr "makes or gets made."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2150"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.7"
msgid "Chabbassāni dhāretabbanti"
msgstr "He should keep it for six years:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.8"
msgid "chabbassaparamatā dhāretabbaṃ."
msgstr "he should keep it for a minimum of six years."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2151"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.9"
msgid "Orena ce channaṃ vassānanti"
msgstr "In less than six years:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.10"
msgid "ūnakachabbassāni."
msgstr "fewer than six years."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2152"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.11"
msgid "Taṃ santhataṃ vissajjetvāti"
msgstr "That blanket has been given away:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.12"
msgid "aññesaṃ datvā."
msgstr "it has been given to others."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2153"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.13"
msgid "Avissajjetvāti"
msgstr "Not:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.14"
msgid "na kassaci datvā."
msgstr "it has not been given to anyone."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2154"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.15"
msgid "Aññatra bhikkhusammutiyāti"
msgstr "except if the monks have agreed:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.16"
msgid ""
"ṭhapetvā bhikkhusammutiṃ aññaṃ navaṃ santhataṃ karoti vā kārāpeti vā, payoge "
"dukkaṭaṃ."
msgstr ""
"for the act of making another new blanket, or getting one made, unless he "
"has the permission of the monks, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.17"
msgid "Paṭilābhena nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When he gets the blanket, it becomes subject to relinquishment."

#. </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.18"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr ""
"The blanket should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.19"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. <span class="pe"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.20"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""
"To be expanded as in <a class=\"cr\" href=\"./pli-tv-bu-vb-np1#13\">"
"Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17</a>, with appropriate substitutions. …"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.21"
msgid ""
"“idaṃ me, bhante, santhataṃ ūnakachabbassāni kārāpitaṃ, aññatra "
"bhikkhusammutiyā, nissaggiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘Venerables, this blanket which I got made after less than six years without "
"the permission of the monks is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.22"
msgid "Imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.23"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.82"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.24"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.25"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this blanket back to you.’”"

#. </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.25a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2155"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.26"
msgid "Attanā vippakataṃ attanā pariyosāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he finishes what he began himself, he commits an offense entailing "
"relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.27"
msgid "Attanā vippakataṃ parehi pariyosāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he gets others to finish what he began himself, he commits an offense "
"entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.28"
msgid "Parehi vippakataṃ attanā pariyosāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he finishes himself what was begun by others, he commits an offense "
"entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.29"
msgid "Parehi vippakataṃ parehi pariyosāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he gets others to finish what was begun by others, he commits an offense "
"entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.29a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2156"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.30"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.31"
msgid "chabbassāni karoti,"
msgstr "if he makes one after six years;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.32"
msgid "atirekachabbassāni karoti,"
msgstr "if he makes one after more than six years;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.33"
msgid "aññassatthāya karoti vā kārāpeti vā,"
msgstr "if he makes one, or gets one made, for the sake of another;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.34"
msgid "aññena kataṃ paṭilabhitvā paribhuñjati,"
msgstr "if he obtains what was made by another and then uses it;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.35"
msgid ""
"vitānaṃ vā bhūmattharaṇaṃ vā sāṇipākāraṃ vā bhisiṃ vā bibbohanaṃ vā karoti,"
msgstr ""
"if he makes a canopy, a floor cover, a screen-wall, a mattress, or a pillow;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.36"
msgid "bhikkhusammutiyā,"
msgstr "if he has the permission of the monks;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.37"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.38"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2157"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:pts-cs3.39"
msgid "Chabbassasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ."
msgstr "The fourth rule, the training rule on six years, is finished."

